modules.name: AWS.CloudHSMV2
modules.comments: For more information about AWS CloudHSM, see AWS CloudHSM and the AWS CloudHSM User Guide.

declarations.comments: Creates a new AWS CloudHSM cluster.
declarations.title: createCluster

declarations.comments: Creates a new hardware security module (HSM) in the specified AWS CloudHSM cluster.
declarations.title: createHsm

declarations.comments: Deletes the specified AWS CloudHSM cluster. Before you can delete a cluster, you must delete all HSMs in the cluster. To see if the cluster contains any HSMs, use DescribeClusters. To delete an HSM, use DeleteHsm.
declarations.title: deleteCluster

declarations.comments: Deletes the specified HSM. To specify an HSM, you can use its identifier (ID), the IP address of the HSM's elastic network interface (ENI), or the ID of the HSM's ENI. You need to specify only one of these values. To find these values, use DescribeClusters.
declarations.title: deleteHsm

declarations.comments:
Gets information about backups of AWS CloudHSM clusters.

This is a paginated operation, which means that each response might contain only a subset of all the backups. When the response contains only a subset of backups, it includes a NextToken value. Use this value in a subsequent DescribeBackups request to get more backups. When you receive a response with no NextToken (or an empty or null value), that means there are no more backups to get.
declarations.title: describeBackups

declarations.comments:
Gets information about AWS CloudHSM clusters.

This is a paginated operation, which means that each response might contain only a subset of all the clusters. When the response contains only a subset of clusters, it includes a NextToken value. Use this value in a subsequent DescribeClusters request to get more clusters. When you receive a response with no NextToken (or an empty or null value), that means there are no more clusters to get.
declarations.title: describeClusters

declarations.comments: Claims an AWS CloudHSM cluster by submitting the cluster certificate issued by your issuing certificate authority (CA) and the CA's root certificate. Before you can claim a cluster, you must sign the cluster's certificate signing request (CSR) with your issuing CA. To get the cluster's CSR, use DescribeClusters.
declarations.title: initializeCluster

declarations.comments:
Gets a list of tags for the specified AWS CloudHSM cluster.

This is a paginated operation, which means that each response might contain only a subset of all the tags. When the response contains only a subset of tags, it includes a NextToken value. Use this value in a subsequent ListTags request to get more tags. When you receive a response with no NextToken (or an empty or null value), that means there are no more tags to get.
declarations.title: listTags

declarations.comments: Adds or overwrites one or more tags for the specified AWS CloudHSM cluster.
declarations.title: tagResource

declarations.comments: Removes the specified tag or tags from the specified AWS CloudHSM cluster.
declarations.title: untagResource

declarations.comments: Contains information about a backup of an AWS CloudHSM cluster.
declarations.title: Backup

declarations.comments: Contains one or more certificates or a certificate signing request (CSR).
declarations.title: Certificates

declarations.comments: The request was rejected because the requester does not have permission to perform the requested operation.
declarations.title: CloudHsmAccessDeniedException

declarations.comments: The request was rejected because of an AWS CloudHSM internal failure. The request can be retried.
declarations.title: CloudHsmInternalFailureException

declarations.comments: The request was rejected because it is not a valid request.
declarations.title: CloudHsmInvalidRequestException

declarations.comments: The request was rejected because it refers to a resource that cannot be found.
declarations.title: CloudHsmResourceNotFoundException

declarations.comments: The request was rejected because an error occurred.
declarations.title: CloudHsmServiceException

declarations.comments: Contains information about an AWS CloudHSM cluster.
declarations.title: Cluster

declarations.comments: Contains information about a hardware security module (HSM) in an AWS CloudHSM cluster.
declarations.title: Hsm

declarations.comments: Contains a tag. A tag is a key-value pair.
declarations.title: Tag
